going to go ahead and I’m going to remove
a little bit of bulk through the top area

00:00:16.510 --> 00:00:23.550
here. First we’re going to start in the
back I’m going to start at the bottom, first

00:00:23.550 --> 00:00:28.259
we’re going to do this with the razor and
then later we’re going to go in with the

00:00:28.259 --> 00:00:33.180
notching shears. Now in through here when
I look I see that the color isn’t blending

00:00:33.180 --> 00:00:39.510
so well this is something I can use my razor
to do to help blend in those colors so it

00:00:39.510 --> 00:00:47.400
doesn’t look choppy and also remove bulk
at the same time. I lightly hold my razor

00:00:47.400 --> 00:01:24.840
when working I can always go and take more
out, now I’m going to up in through here

00:01:24.840 --> 00:01:32.759
and when you’re up in this area you very,
very, very lightly razor and this takes out

00:01:32.759 --> 00:01:45.649
some of the bulk it’ll give more volume.
